{"team": "warriors", "url": "https://www.nba.com/warriors/news-blogs/warriors-sound-2015-finals-game-4-20200407", "date": "2020-04-03 00:00:00", "tags": ["Warriors", "Warriors Sound", "GSW History"], "article": " Concerns over the spread of COVID-19 have impacted our everyday lives throughout Dub Nation. As we navigate this unprecedented situation together, the Warriors want to share some feel-good content in the midst of these uncertain times. June 11, 2015 in Cleveland was a turning point in the Warriors' 2015 NBA Finals series with the Cavaliers and it all began with a great start. Down 2-1 entering Game 4, the decision to give eventual Finals MVP Andre Iguodala his first start of the season would prove to be key to the game and a major storyline in the series. That Thursday night in Ohio, Iguodala and Stephen Curry each scored 22 points on the way to a 103-82 win that tied the series at two-all with Game 5 set for Oracle Arena that coming Sunday. In this Warriors Sound Flashback, listen to a full game recap where Warriors Head Coach Steve Kerr, Iguodala and Curry all talk about the win, plus hear Draymond Green discuss the series momentum-changing victory with Tim Roye and Tom Tolbert on the Warriors Radio Network postgame show. You will now recieve Warriors Insider emails! Please check your inbox for a confirmation message We received an error message while processing your submission. Please make sure all the fields are filled out correctly and try again. "}
