{"team": "warriors", "url": "https://www.nba.com/warriors/news-blogs/dubs-daily-20200327", "date": "2020-03-27 00:00:00", "tags": ["Warriors", "Dubs Daily"], "article": " Though the current NBA season remains on hold, NBC Sports Bay Area will re-air classic Warriors games every night at 8 p.m. beginning Friday with a memorable Klay performance as determined by fan vote. While awaiting the memorable games, read up on the latest team news and headlines in the latest Dubs Daily: The Starting Five. Mike Brown and Nigerian national team find silver lining in delay of OlympicsThe postponement of the Tokyo 2020 Olympics give Warriors assistant coach and head coach of the Nigerian men\u2019s basketball extra time to build a roster and staff for the games. \u00bb Read Full Story Steve Kerr on 95.7 The GameDubs Head Coach Steve Kerr had high praise for Stephen Curry after the guard\u2019s COVID-19 Q&amp;A with Dr. Anthony Fauci: \u201c\u201cI said to Bob [Myers], \u2018Can you imagine having a better representative for our organization?\u2019\u201d \u00bb Listen to Interview Warriors All-21st Century Team: Steph Curry, Kevin Durant highlight squadMonte Poole creates a 15-man roster of his All-21st Century Team, which includes Dubs from the recent NBA Championship teams and the We Believe era. \u00bb Read Full Story Steve Kerr on KNBRFrom how the staff is studying free agents to what he is looking for in players coming through the NBA Draft, Warriors Head Coach Steve Kerr talks about how the team is preparing for the summer. \u00bb Listen to Interview Does Klay Thompson perform better in Game 6s? Redditor u/FBZOMBiES explored the phenomenon known as \u201cGame 6 Klay\u201d to find if Klay Thompson does perform at a higher level in Game 6 scenarios. \u00bb Read on Reddit  u/FBZOMBiES looked into whether Klay's given moniker, \"Game 6 Klay\" is valid. Here are his averages since that legendary 2016 OKC Game 6 that christened him.In Game 6s, Klay puts up 27.8ppg on .487/.538/.818